---
description: Shell script conventions and compatibility
globs:
  - "**/*.sh"
  - "**/*.bash"
  - "**/*.zsh"
  - "**/*.fish"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Shell Scripts

- Prefer heredoc over multiple echo/print statements
- Ensure compatibility with both bash/zsh and fish shells
- Prevent trailing whitespace in generated files
- Use POSIX syntax in `.sh` files (`!` not `not`, `$?` not `$status`)
- Use Fish syntax only in `.fish` files
